Environment Identification
Use these variables or functions to check if your script is running on Eazyy Sploit.

Variables
eazysploit (bool): true
easysploit (bool): true (shorthand)
eazyy (bool): true (shorthand)
Functions
identifyexecutor()
Returns: string (Name), string (Version)
Example:

lua
local name, version = identifyexecutor()
print("Running " .. name .. " v" .. version)
getexecutorname()
Returns: string ("Eazyy Sploit")

getexecutorversion()
Returns: string ("2.0")

isluraw()
Returns: bool (true) - Used for compatibility with many open-source scripts.

Clipboard Utilities
Interact with the system's clipboard.

setclipboard(text: string)
Copies the provided text to the user's PC clipboard. Example: setclipboard("https://discord.gg/eazyy")

toclipboard(text: string)
Alias for setclipboard.

Sandboxed Filesystem
All file operations are strictly sandboxed within the Eazyy\Workspace folder for security.

makefolder(path: string)
Creates a new directory. Example: makefolder("MyData")

listfiles(folder: string)
Returns: table (List of filenames)
Lists all files and subfolders in the specified directory. Example: local files = listfiles("MyData")

delfile(path: string)
Deletes a specific file. Example: delfile("temp.txt")

delfolder(path: string)
Deletes a folder and all its contents. Example: delfolder("OldData")

Editor Shorthands (In-Editor Only)
Type these directly into the Eazyy Sploit script editor and press Execute.

Shorthand	Action
inf-yield	Loads the Infinite Yield admin script.
dex
Loads the remote Dark Dex game explorer.
Developer Tools
Dex Explorer: A built-in high-performance object explorer (O(1) lookups).
Remote Spy: Logs all RemoteEvent/RemoteFunction calls with arguments and timing.
Nil Instance Explorer: Allows viewing objects not parented to game.
